{{Infobox book | name = Barracoon: The Story of the Last "Black Cargo" | image = Barracoon The Story of the Last Black Cargo cover.jpg | caption = Hardcover edition | author = [[Zora Neale Hurston]] | country = United States | language = English | subject = Biography of the last known survivor of the Atlantic slave trade | genre = [[Nonfiction]] | publisher = [[Amistad Press]] | release_date = May 8, 2018 | isbn = 9780062748201 | oclc = | pages = 208 }}
'''''Barracoon: The Story of the Last "Black Cargo"''''' is a non-fiction work by [[Zora Neale Hurston]]. It is based on her interviews in 1927 with [[Cudjo Lewis]], the last living survivor of the [[Middle Passage]].<ref name=vulture>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vulture.com/2018/04/zora-neale-hurston-barracoon-excerpt.html|title=Zora Neale Hurston's Lost Interview with One of Americ's Last Living Slaves |work=[[Vulture (magazine)|Vulture]] |access-date=2018-05-01|language=en}}</ref> The book failed to find a publisher at the time, in part because it was written in [[vernacular]], and also in part because it described the involvement of other African people in the business of [[Atlantic slave trade]].<ref name=vulture/>
The manuscript, which was in the [[Alain Locke]] Collection at the [[Moorland-Spingarn Research Center]], [[Howard University]], remained unpublished until the 21st century.<ref name=guardian>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/dec/19/zora-neale-hurston-study-of-last-survivor-of-us-slave-trade-to-be-published|title=Zora Neale Hurston study of last survivor of US slave trade to be published|last=Flood|first=Alison|date=2017-12-19|website=[[The Guardian]] |location=London |language=en|access-date=2018-05-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Diouf|first1=Sylviane A.|title=Cudjo Lewis|url=http://www.encyclopediaofalabama.org/article/h-1403|website=Encyclopedia of Alabama|accessdate=1 May 2018|date=2009}}</ref> Excerpts from the book were first published in ''[[Wrapped in Rainbows: The Life of Zora Neale Hurston]]'', a biography of Hurston by [[Valerie Boyd]].<ref name=guardian/> The full book was published in 2018.<ref name="NPR">{{cite news|last1=Neary|first1=Lynn|title=Zora Neale Hurston's 'Barracoon' Gets Published, More Than 60 Years Later|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/05/05/608723606/zora-neale-hurstons-barracoon-gets-published-more-than-60-years-later|accessdate=2018-05-11|publisher=[[NPR]] |work=[[Weekend Edition Saturday]] |date=2018-05-02}}</ref>
